Simple Rule-Based Chatbot (Python)
 Overview
This is a **beginner-friendly chatbot** built using Python’s `if-elif-else` statements.  
It simulates a simple conversation and responds to basic inputs like greetings, questions, and exit commands.

This project is perfect for **beginners** who want to learn how chatbots work **without using AI or machine learning**.
🚀 Features:
✅ Responds to basic greetings (`hi`, `hello`, `hey`)  
✅ Answers simple questions like “What is your name?” and “How are you?”  
✅ Allows users to exit by typing `bye`, `exit`, or `quit`  
✅ Handles unknown inputs with a polite fallback message  
Installation & Usage:
1️⃣ Clone the repository
bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/chatbot.git
cd chatbot
